abstract: Under one proposal, the Senate could convene earlier on Saturday and then hold a shorter session, allowing members to travel home or hit the campaign trail.
snippet: Under one proposal, the Senate could convene earlier on Saturday and then hold a shorter session, allowing members to travel home or hit the campaign trail.
lead_paragraph: As senators settled in for another long day of arguments from the House managers, there was already talk among lawmakers and their aides of a potentially abbreviated weekend trial schedule.

abstract: In the clip, Mr. Graham gave a broad definition of a “high crime.”
snippet: In the clip, Mr. Graham gave a broad definition of a “high crime.”
lead_paragraph: Senator Lindsey Graham, Republican of South Carolina and one of the impeachment managers in 1999, left the Senate chamber just minutes before House Democrats played a video of him speaking during President Bill Clinton’s trial.
headline_main: Senator Lindsey Graham misses a clip of a speech he made during Clinton’s trial in 1999.

abstract: As he runs for president, Mr. Biden has repeatedly faced questions about the overseas business dealings of his son, Hunter Biden. He has mostly kept his cool — but not always.
snippet: As he runs for president, Mr. Biden has repeatedly faced questions about the overseas business dealings of his son, Hunter Biden. He has mostly kept his cool — but not always.
lead_paragraph: SPARKS, Nev. — Joseph R. Biden Jr. called an octogenarian voter a “damn liar” and challenged him to a push-up contest. He dismissed a heckler as an “idiot.” He commanded the news media to focus on President Trump instead of the overseas business dealings of his son, Hunter Biden, demanding of one reporter, “Ask the right question!”

abstract: Vice President Mike Pence has invited the prime minister of Israel and an opposition leader to visit Washington next week.
snippet: Vice President Mike Pence has invited the prime minister of Israel and an opposition leader to visit Washington next week.
lead_paragraph: As Democrats spoke in the Senate, Vice President Mike Pence announced that President Trump had asked him to invite to Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel to Washington next week to discuss “regional issues, as well as the prospect of peace here in the Holy Land.”

headline_main: The administration’s work goes on, with an invitation to Israel’s leader.

abstract: Just as the Democrats’ presentation resumed, the president tweeted about the proceedings.
snippet: Just as the Democrats’ presentation resumed, the president tweeted about the proceedings.
lead_paragraph: Just as Representative Jerrold Nadler of New York, a House manager, started his presentation about “high crimes and misdemeanors,” President Trump started tweeting, accusing Democrats of not wanting to agree to a trade in which the Senate would subpoena several administration officials in exchange for people Mr. Trump’s allies have said they want. Two people Republicans have sought to interview are Hunter Biden, the son of the former vice president, and the anonymous whistle-blower who first expressed concerns about Mr. Trump’s July 25 call with the president of Ukraine.
headline_main: Is President Trump watching the trial?

abstract: The invitation could provide a welcome distraction for President Trump, facing an impeachment trial, and for Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, who is facing corruption charges.
snippet: The invitation could provide a welcome distraction for President Trump, facing an impeachment trial, and for Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, who is facing corruption charges.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — President Trump said Thursday that he would release his long-awaited Middle East peace plan within days and invited Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel and his rival, the former army chief Benny Gantz, to the White House next week to discuss it.

abstract: In Davos, business leaders were newly vocal about the danger, though they gave few details about how they would reform their practices.
snippet: In Davos, business leaders were newly vocal about the danger, though they gave few details about how they would reform their practices.
lead_paragraph: DAVOS, Switzerland — Business titans who for decades brushed off warnings about climate change arrived at the annual World Economic Forum this week ready to show their newfound enthusiasm for the cause.

abstract: The Afghan leader said he had told President Trump that the United States could withdraw a third of its troops, even as a peace deal with Taliban remains elusive.
snippet: The Afghan leader said he had told President Trump that the United States could withdraw a third of its troops, even as a peace deal with Taliban remains elusive.
lead_paragraph: DAVOS, Switzerland — Afghanistan is prepared for a major reduction in United States forces there, President Ashraf Ghani said on Thursday, adding that he had given that message to President Trump, a step toward winding down the costly American military presence as diplomats struggle to finalize a peace deal with the Taliban.
